<TITLE> Film stars to play charity football match Friday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 11 (bdnews24.com)  Stars of the silver screen will play a charity football match against former star booters August 17 in a bid to raise funds for the flood-affected people. "We want everyone to stand by the flood-affected people and hope everyone will extend their hands to the flood-affected people by their presences at the charity football match Friday," said general secretary of the film actor and actresses' association Manna at a press conference at the National Sports Council (NSC) Saturday. Before the match between the stars and the former star booters, another match between popular Abahani Limited and Mohammedan SC will also be held at the Bangabandhu National Stadium (BNS) at 5pm. The price of the match tickets is yet to be fixed, said the speakers adding that Bobita, Suchanda, Champa, Riaz, Ferdous, Mousumi, Shanu, Ahmed Sharif, Suruj Bangali and Teli Samad would be present on the match day at the BNS. President of film actor and actresses' association Mizu Ahmed, president of the film directors' association Shawkat Jamil and general secretary Shah Alam, Abahani director Kazi Nabil Ahmed, Brothers Union general secretary Mijanuddin Ahmed and Mohammedan additional general secretary Mostaqur Rahman were among others present at the press conference. 
